<br />

<br />
<span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal">4) Improved Damage shield </span>
<br />

<br />
<span style="color: red">Currently being discussed</span>
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal">5) Streamline the item summoning process (more target summons) </span>
<br />

<br />
<span style="color: red">The current plan is to implement this change before Omens of War launches</span>
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal">6) Allow suspended pets to zone, OR allow pets to remain with their master while the master is invisible.  (Pet Issues/Requests)</span> 
<br />

<br />
<span style="color: red">Dev notes - An AA that upgrades Suspend Minion to allow a suspended pet to zone is under consideration for a future expansion</span>
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal">7) Improve pet Heals. (Pet Issues/Requests) </span>
<br />

<br />
<span style="color: blue">Currently being discussed</span>
<br />
  
<br />
<span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal">8) Revamp pet focus availability. (Pet Issues/Requests) </span>
<br />

<br />
<span style="color: blue">Currently being discussed</span>
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal">9) COH useable in more zones. (make CoTH available in all corpse summoning zones) </span>
<br />

<br />
<span style="color: blue">Currently being discussed</span>
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal">10) Better utility in groups and raids </span>
<br />
 
<br />
<span style="color: red">Currently being discussed</span>
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-size: 24px; line-height: normal">Details on #2</span>
<br />

<br />
1) Elemental Agility- This AA is broken.
<br />

<br />
<span style="color: blue">No Status Update</span>
<br />

<br />
2) Elemental Forms –
<br />

<br />
<span style="color: red">No changes planned at this time</span>
<br />

<br />
3) Mass Group Buff –
<br />

<br />
4) Quick MGB –
<br />

<br />
<span style="color: red">Addition not being considered at this time.</span>
<br />

<br />
5) Frenzied Burnout –
<br />

<br />
6) Turn Summoned –
<br />

<br />
<span style="color: red">Currently being discussed</span>
<br />

<br />
7) Elemental Pact –
<br />

<br />
<span style="color: red">This is something coding will not allow at this time, however it is something that may be considered in the future as code allows</span>
<br />

<br />
8) Host of the Elements –
<br />

<br />
<span style="color: red">Currently being discussed</span>
<br />

<br />
9) Mend Companion -
<br />

<br />
<span style="color: red"> Dev notes - Mend Companion, like normal mend, is a percent based heal.  It scales with the pet.  Beyond that, if Mend won’t soak a single round of melee damage, then the problem isn’t in mend.  Upgrading it means the pet lives an extra 3 seconds.</span>
<br />

<br />
(Mod Note: They incorrectly labeled Mend Companion as a percentage based heal. Its a fixed heal equal to 33 x Level +1 of the magician. The percentage healed on the pet varies with the pet itself as well as the focus and buffs on it.)
<br />

<br />
10) Secondary Forte -
<br />

<br />
<span style="color: red">No changes planned at this time
<br />
Dev notes - Any further decrease in mana cost is going to come at a premium and in small chunks.</span>
<br />

<br />
11) Shared Health -
<br />

<br />
<span style="color: red">Currently being discussed</span>
<br />

<br />
12) Elemental Alacrity -
<br />

<br />
<span style="color: red">Currently being evaluated</span>
<br />

<br />
13) Healing Adept/Gift/Adv Adept/Adv Gift -
<br />

<br />
14) Quick Damage -
<br />

<br />
<span style="color: red">Currently being considered as an addition with future expansions</span>
<br />

<br />
15) Spell Casting Reinforcement/SCR Mastery -
<br />

<br />
<span style="color: red">Dev notes - They have a few buffs, but so do wizards and necromancers and they don’t have it either.</span></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
