			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hello all!
<br />

<br />
After playing EQ for 5 years, I can definitely leave some real input here.  Most of my rants/raves have to do with just one topic - Quillmane.  Due to the changes in the servers, Quillmane no longer spawns. There are no longer 200+ people in South Karana killing everything in site.  Quillmane has to be changed from a triggered spawn to a timed spawn so he at least appears a few times a day. I have not seen him for over 5 months now.  Secondarily, I would like to see an alternate form of the cloak from Quillmane, one that is Magician only, just for our quests, and is tradable.  Too many people hoard the current cloak, thinking they are going to get an easy 5k or 10k for it shortly.  They do not realize that they have to visit the Air plane - often with a guild raid - and hang around until the Mage has his or her crown.  This is the WORST part of the Magician quests.  I say this as I finally approach being able to get my Magician epic - as a casual player.  5 years in the making, and I'm only missing two things - Quillmane's cloak and the Crown from Air.  Pretty shabby in that after killing Quillmane probably close to 80 times, I have ONLY received the stupid leggings from him!
<br />

<br />
Now, for some critism of Sony here.  On Sony's own boards for the Magicians, I went back to JANUARY of this year.  NONE of the items listed in JANUARY of this year were ever (a) addressed or (b) given to the Magician community.  Going back even further, I realized that NOTHING was ever done for the Magician community based on our requests.  The list being compiled right now is the SAME list that has been floating around forever.  NOTHING has ever been done with it.
<br />

<br />
How do we make our voices heard?
<br />

<br />
Peronally, I am at the point of final reckoning.  If OoW requires me to buy another computer just to keep up with the graphics requirements, I am out of here.  Sony has done NOTHING at all these for Magicians.  I think it's about time to do the same thing to Sony - for nothing given, you get nothing from me in return, ever again.  It's time to turn to another game that WILL listen to it's users and also have developers that actually PLAY the game and all of it's classes and actually know what's really going on in-game.
<br />

<br />
It is pathetic that non-developers can actually define and describe with hard facts what spells and effects and AA's are actually doing, and a developer - someone who should KNOW this - spouts nonsense.  It is almost as if they gave the Magicians a PR person with a "fact sheet" to read off of.  IT IS INSULTING!!!!
<br />

<br />
As a programmer myself, I expect a different type of professionalism from the field.  This professionalism is definitely lacking for the most part.
<br />

<br />
Okay, now that I've got my rants out of the way - what about the list?  I agree for the most part with the list.  I would add my peeves about Quillmane to the list.  Aside from Quillmane, I think these are the top issues that I would like to see fixed:
<br />

<br />
2) Overhaul class specific AA's. 
<br />
Definitely needs to be done!  Too many useless AAs or underpowered AAs for the cost here.  Some things would be better as disciplines rather than have them here.  I think Shared Health should be changed from a timed AA to something that is always active, or a toggle - if you have it on, it is always on.  And I think that the range of it's effect should be Line of Sight, not direct contact.  Direct contact is just plain silly, especially when dealing with magic.
<br />

<br />
6) Allow susended pets to zone, OR allow pets to remain with their master while the master is invisible. (Pet Issues/Requests) 
<br />
Definitely allow the suspended pets to zone.  It is a no-brainer and actually very stupid that they did not do this in the first place.  As a matter of fact, I had had MANY NUMEROUS direct discussions with the developers BEFORE the zoning pets even came out to make sure that when it did, the suspended pets zoned as well.  As for pets remaining with their master that their master is invisible - well - I could see that with the Air pet since they see invisibe, but it should not be possible with other pets, unless they have something that lets them see the invisible.  I could live with that limitation.  I am thinking about lower level Mages - they could benefit from this ability.  At the higher levels, well, suspend minion sort of handles this....
<br />

<br />
10) Better utility in groups and raids 
<br />
Give us some more buffs we can cast on others, or allow us to summon USEFUL items, like player usable weapons of mass destruction, player usable uber armor and shields, player usable manastones, player uable stat food;  allow our pet spells to affect group or raid pets, give us an AA so our self-only buffs can be cast on others, etc. etc.
<br />

<br />
The one item I think people have missed a few things on is:
<br />

<br />
7) Improve pet Heals. (Pet Issues/Requests)
<br />
I agree there should be two more pet heals - a level 65 HoT to help reduce overall mana costs to keep the pet healed and a CH type , BUT I think a lot of people have either ignored or do not use the lower level spells.  I do not have the LoY HoT spell yet - I have to complete this quest one day - but armed with that, the regular heal, a lower level heal, and the condition remover, you are set to go with your pet.  If you play yourself like a cleric, especially with the HoT and some casting time reductions on your side, you can be a pretty effective pet healer.  What is really needed is you have to train your party members to offer the occasional heal to pets, or to treat your pet as the main tank.  Sometimes the pet's survival is the key between sucess and a wipe in a bad fight.  I should know.  I am usually the last or 2nd to last person in a RAID to die when there is a wipe...  That is PET POWER!  If the healers in the raids had focused on the pets after the main tanks died, there would have been fewer wipes...
<br />

<br />
So, there you have it.  All my rants and raves and criticisms, but just about the Magician class.  I have many other gripes just about some mechanics of the game itself, but that's not for here.  Hopefully others will let their voices be heard as well!</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
