				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">My biggest concern is the overuse of "This is being discussed."
<br />

<br />
Honestly?  I'd rather they just come out and say "Yeah, sorry, haven't looked at that yet."    Sucky answer, true, but at least it's forthright.
<br />

<br />
As others have said, some of these are simple, 1 or 2 db entry changes.   Cutting the spell recast time on heals (even PR) is one update statement and one commit.   And while this doesn't completely fix anything healing-balance related between us and other pet classes, it does move in the right direction.
<br />

<br />
Yes, I want pets that make mobs have to change their pants when Jabober comes tearing towards them.   No, I don't think having to buy more expansions to get balance is a good thing.  There's currently no reason for me to "reward" Sony for their work, heck, if I could, I'd get a refund on GoD.
<br />

<br />
I'm glad the dev team is working hard on making sure OOW is going to be smooth, but what good is a smooth release of a new expansion to the existing issues?   Will I suddenly magically become wanted again because I've bought the expansion?
<br />

<br />
